parent.description: A category that is the parent of this category in the category tree.

naturalId.description: The naturalKey for all caches {@link CacheImpl} and {@link BeanImpl}

assetClass.description: The key to resolve an asset class

childs.description: The child categories derived from the parent value.

packageGroup.description: Defines to which group a model belong e.g. asset/cache/action

hostCache.description: The field for hostCache e.g. defined in {@link FileCache}

action.description: A value extending the {@link Action} Class.

model.description: The simple name of the class referenced as first value of the {@link ModelsList}

join.description: A reference key to a id field for joining.

colKeys.description: The key list for mapping values in a value list.

write.description: String representation of RolePermission write permissions

models.description: A string representation for a list of model keys.

hibernateAnnotations.description: sets a Flag for using hibernate annotations when bean is created.

streetNumber.description: The streetnumber is a string to include street numbers like 1a

addressMap.description: A map of addresses with a n-m relation in {@link Customer}

module.description: Defines a target module where generating occurs.

version.description: The current version of the category.

execute.description: String representation of RolePermission execute permissions

ignoreHeader.description: Ignore the setting of a header.

lineItemList.description: A list of lineItems for an order

whereAsString.description: Where to be set as a String

schema.description: The database schema used for persisting. {@link HostCache}

lastName.description: The last name of a person.

subTestList.description: A generic parametrized example List with {@link SubTest}

cacheKey.description: The key to resolve an cache entry

orderHint.description: An attribute as base for a custom category order in one level.

configFile.description: A hibernate property which defines the location of a xml mapping configuration file.

cached.description: If true will cache the readed file within the cache object.

table.description: The name of the persistence entity in {@link ModelCache} or the join table in {@link FieldCache}.

assetAction.description: The key to resolve an action

productOrderMap.description: A map of orders with natural id as key.

modelKey.description: The model name for the bean/action object {@link Bean}.

cacheModel.description: Checks if model is a cache model

mapPath.description: A key for the super class of a class.

country.description: A two-digit country code as per  ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 .

auto.description: A hibernate property which defines the creation type of the database, e.g. update or create.

integer.description: A non unique integer value for alias.

assetKey.description: The key to resolve an asset

fieldBeanMap.description: A list of field beans referenced by the key of the field. {@link FieldBean}

fileCache.description: The field for hostCache e.g. defined in {@link CsvCache}

fieldCacheMap.description: A list of field cache objects referenced by the name of the field. {@link FieldCache}

actionMap.description: An object map preparing value setting in the action implementation. (new)

actionKey.description: The key to resolve an action

create.description: String representation of RolePermission create permissions

modelBeanKey.description: The model name for the cache object {@link Bean}.

slug.description: must match the pattern [-a-zA-Z0-9_]{2,256} human-readable identifiers usually used as deep-link URL to the related category. Each slug is unique across a project, but a category can have the same slug for different languages.

read.description: String representation of RolePermission read permissions

author.description: The autor of something e,g. a class.

superKey.description: A key for the super class of a class.

modelsList.description: A list of models to specify field types.

propertyMap.description: A map of properties for the product.

creationDate.description: Used to define the creation of an item.

firstName.description: The first name of a person.

idKey.description: The id key defined in modelsList

subModule.description: Defines the target  sub module like 'main' or 'test'.

testString.description: Just a small test string used in test models.

joinInverse.description: A self reference key to a id field on a glue n-m table.

fieldName.description: A name for different purposes depending on the model.

modelCacheKey.description: The model name for the cache object {@link Cache}.

genericModel.description: The name of the class referenced as first value of the {@link ModelsList} with a generic set when map/list.

origin.description: The key to resolve an cache entry

description.description: A description of the model used by every model extending BaseClassImpl.

delete.description: String representation of RolePermission delete permissions

useAdapterValues.description: Use adapter values for creating filter conditions.

expanded.description: For creating a cache using only bean fields.

propertyType.description: A reference to the property type like string or number.

scope.description: A scope for the cache value.

value.description: A value for a property as String.

interfaces.description: A comma separeted list of interface keys.

quantity.description: The quantity e.g. of a LineItem

or.description: A list of {@link And} condition list

actionParams.description: A List of action params for create actions depending on action and asset key

subTestMap.description: A generic parametrized example Map with {@link SubTest}

boolean.description: A pattern for boolean field alias.

customerMap.description: A map of customers with a n-m relation in {@link Address}.

properties.description: Hibernate properties which are not specified by instance var.
